## Decisions made
- 3-step wizard, not 4. cp4 closes at the READY preview screen; the
  `/done` route ships with slice 7 alongside POST commit. The commit
  button is rendered but disabled with a tooltip pointing at slice 7,
  so admins see what's coming without being able to fire it.
- Bridge step 1 → step 2 via sessionStorage (jobId-keyed) rather than
  extending the GET DTO with headers/sampleRows. Cheap, contained,
  doesn't broaden the public surface for a fringe case. Refresh-resume
  across browser sessions is deferred. The mapping page redirects
  back to /students/import if sessionStorage is empty on mount.
- Auto-guess mapping via a local synonym table (`lib/imports/synonyms.ts`)
  rather than calling out to the server. Synonyms are case-insensitive
  + punctuation-stripped; the auto-guess refuses to claim a target
  field twice so the wizard never starts in a duplicate-mapping state.
  Admin overrides every guess via the dropdown.
- Bad-rows download uses an in-memory blob + `<a download>` click
  (the only browser-native way to attach the Authorization header to a
  binary download). The endpoint already returns the right
  Content-Disposition; we parse the filename out of it and fall back
  to a sensible default.

